board.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>But seriously, I believe Talovar is planning on leading the first CoG Severilous raid - his confidance in our ability to take Sev down is the reason I added us to the rotation.<br><br>As the time of that first Sev raid approaches, I expect either Tal or myself will make a few posts about what gear to bring, what level requirements are, what tactics we'll use... that kind of thing. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwarriorrmog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorRmog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/9/01 9:31:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Severilous is lev 60<br>His pet is lev 39<br><br>He is a shaman.<br><br>His maximum melee damage is 520 <br>He uses magic based area fear <br>He uses poison based area stun <br><br>32K HP<br><br>Seems like it is very hard to resist his AoE stun.  His fear is hard to res also.<br><br>Some cheep PR gear:<br><br>1.) Golden Pearl Necklace (5 AC, +9 PR, ALL/ALL) <br>approx cost of components: 16p <br><br>2.) Platinum Pearl Rings x 2 (4 AC, +10 PR, ALL/ALL) <br>approx cost of components: 115p (per ring) <br><br>3.) Golden Malachite Bracers (+5 PR, ALL/ALL) <br>approx cost of components: 11p (per bracer - don't forget that a hero bracer is +5 PR <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I got almost of this info off Illia's bestiary.  (Ok ok, all of it)<br><br>Hope it helps.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/9/01 9:52:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Ummmm...I admire the chutzpah that went into adding us to the Sev rotation Kommisar.  However, 1 point.<br><br>According to KGC rules we CANNOT have anyone who is in a guild/alliance that is part of the Sev rotation.  Which is half the guilds on the server.  Although...looking through the list it doesnt seem like too many of the guilds/alliances are part of guilds that regularly help CoG raids.  I would note, however, I dont know anyone with a rez stick that is not part of a guild on the Sev rotation.  That will kinda be essential unless we can get enough clerics to deal with the mass rez's that we will have to do.<br><br>Resists.  These are absolutely essential.  Everyone, and I mean everyone, will need their appropriate resists above 100.  Probably closer to 125.  Unbuffed.  These things arent like the old world dragons where you can get away with something lower.  These things are harsh.  Dont think you can just slip and not be noticed.  No resists, the raid will fail.<br><br>Still Kommisar, I would've suggested putting us on the VS rotation first in order to test things out.  As hard as VS is, he's slightly easier than Sev, and you dont have to deal with outdoor fears.  *shiver*  On the other hand, if you dont want to do VS, we can always try a few Triggered Faydadear raids  The triggered version of Fay should be about equal to Sev, perhaps a tad harder, but not by much.  While he's a small little smuck, it probably will be good training for everyone.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>Still Crunchy! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueqkommisar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqkommisar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Can-Head</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/9/01 8:20:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.chrometiger.com/~anubis/stuff/canhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Ouch - don't shoot the messenger!  I was talkin to Tal about a couple random things and he suggested we sign up fer the Sev rotation.<br><br>Severilous claws YOU for 200 points of damage.<br>Severilous claws YOU for 520 points of damage.<br>You tell your party, 'oh my god'<br>Severilous kicks YOU for 134 points of damage.<br>Severilous pet tries to bite YOU, but YOU parry!<br>Severilous pet bites YOU for 19 points of damage.<br>Severilous says &quot;Ahah! What did I tell you mortal?  As your life slips away, you may hear me laugh at you.  Ha ha, ha ha, ha ha.   There, now you have learned your lesson.  A pity it is far too late.<br>Severilous claws YOU for 520 points of damage.<br><br>He hit me a couple times before the text I have there starts... but that's all I have from the one screenshot I kept of that uh... incident. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueqkommisar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqkommisar</A> at: 8/9/01 8:23:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utildartreewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tildar Treewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/10/01 11:44:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/tildar/sigpic_20.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> I for one think this is a great idea... <br><br>The KCOG is a wonderful thing and I for one and damn happy you guys are here to help us out. <br><br>I cannot WAIT to get summoned by this guy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=9288">Tildar the Wind Caller</A> <BR> Druid of Tunare <BR><IMG SRC="http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/tildar_50.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueqkommisar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqkommisar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Can-Head</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/10/01 3:43:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.chrometiger.com/~anubis/stuff/canhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Just noticed that Sacred Band isn't on the Sev rotation... if we decide to stay on it and they're not on it by the time we're up... joint raid maybe?  Hmm... bears thinking. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/14/01 9:24:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> I'll talk to the officers and see what we come up with. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/14/01 3:04:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Looks like a distinct possibility, Kommisar. Shoot me an email at haemish@bellsouth.net and we'll talk it over. <br><br>Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulenenaemcgillicuddy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenenae McGillicuddy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/14/01 5:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/lenmug.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Did someone say Res Stick?</span><hr size=1> ...heh, sorry, I jump when I hear that.<br><br>Has anyone played with the thought of getting a dedicated KCoG cleric a res stick?<br><br>I just read that there's a new rule in with the KGC for Naggy/Ragefire, it goes something like, &quot;if you are camping Ragefire, you have to yeild your spot to the naggy raiding guild.&quot; Meaning if you are there to take down Naggy, you have the option of sticking around for the Ragefire spawn as well. (I think, correct me if I'm giddy)<br><br>This would make at least obtaining an epic by the KCoG at least a possibility in the forseeable future.<br><br>Of course being a cleric I'd die to get my hands on one of those things, but I think any cleric that hangs with the KCoG a lot is a good candidate for this. Just a couple &quot;things&quot; standing in the way...<br><br>Ixiblat Fer - level 62, has 32,000 HPs, a gang of magicians are the way to go with him I've heard.<br><br>Overking Bathezid - a level 65 Sarnak Wizard with 32,000 HPs, deep in Chardok, pain in the posterior probably. Probably has Greater Ice Comet or something.<br><br>Ixiblat you have to hand in an item from the quest, so ya gotta be up to that point to make him spawn, and failure means starting over, but Overking can be done whenever. Then ya gotta do Ragefire, then ya got a cleric who can do reses whenever Sev is up.<br><br>How hard could it be, I see these sticks everywhere. OK, totally off topic now, sorry. I'm easily exciteable, as I'm sure is every cleric reading this without their res stick yet. <p>-Lenenae McGillicuddy<br><img src="http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/voxnlen.jpg"><br><i>(Everyone loves a healer)</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/16/01 2:45:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Did someone say Res Stick?</span><hr size=1> Great idea.  Unfortunatly rather poorer in execution.  The problem is simply that even if CoG manages to get a cleric or two equiped with a rez stick there's nothing stopping that cleric from joining an larger guild that cant help us due to rotational restrictions.  I would further point out that part of the cleric epic requires a piece from PoA.  That would be very hard to CoG to get to.<br><br>Now, that being said, there's nothing wrong in requesting CoG help with obtaining YOUR epic.  Indeed there's no reason why you cannot request to take the ragefire camp after CoG takes Naggy down next time.  Of course, you'd have to supply some o fhte raiders since anyone from CoG would be purely volunteers.  And if there are several clerics that want Rage I imagine you'd have to roll against them for the camp.  That'd be up to the Raid Leader tho.  <br><br>So I dont see how CoG could manage to work through and get a cleric an epic.  We can, however, help with specific parts, you just need to lead those raids and post for volunteers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Difficulty.  Ix is fairly hardish.  I know SB recently took a crack at him so they'd know better.  The few times I went was with Forged Alliance and it was fairly simple once we got our coordination in.  Overking, once again fairly hardish.  Main thing is getting your raid together.  Although you might be able to combine that and Ix together.  Rage.  Er...good luck.  The camp is mind numbing, almost as bad as the old Faydadear, and CR is a pain.  Probably the hardest part, however, would be the Weight of the Earth (or whatever it is) from PoA.  Rare drop from the 4th island.  That's a 3 day raid, 8 hours a day, once your up, you cant come back down, same as hate takes a 250pp stone per group, need about 4-6 groups really.  Average expense is something around 600pp per person.  Generally only the larger alliances and guilds do this, so I'd advise making some friends with them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Rez sticks arent the hardest to get, but they're still pretty hard.  The reason you see so many is that most guilds/alliances will drop what they're doing to equip their clerics with them first.  Not only does it make good raid sense, it'll make all other epics easier to get as well.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>Who's up for Fay?  Lol.<br><br>And to clarify, the rule on the guild doing Naggy getting the Ragefire camp isnt really a new rule.  Its really just an extention of the whole concept of a camp.  Rage share's Naggy's spawn point so if Naggy is up, Rage simply cant spawn.  If a mob cannot spawn, you cannot camp it.  Hence, when Naggy appears/spawns whomever was camping Rage automaticlly loses the camp to the guild that comes in to kill Naggy.  Since that guild is already there on top of the spawn point, they get the camp next.  This is generally bad for the poor cleric who just lost their camp after spending 2 days sitting there.  But those are the breaks.  Often clerics will make other arrangements with the next guild coming in.  Most will be as accomodating as possible.  And rarely do fights break out, although it has been known to happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umigg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Migg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/24/01 3:43:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kunark Dragons</span><hr size=1> Probably the hardest part, however, would be the Weight of the Earth (or whatever it is) from PoA. Rare drop from the 4th island. That's a 3 day raid, 8 hours a day, once your up, you cant come back down, same as hate takes a 250pp stone per group, need about 4-6 groups really.<br><br>Sorry I must make a comment .. Not as a flame or anything but obviously you dont know anything about a cleric epic.. there is no part of a cleric epic that comes from PoA.. let alone any alter plane.  Cleric epic is one of the easiest epics to do .. next to rogue epic.. the only problem with it is that bottle neck at the end.. RF!!! man that is a nasty camp but not hard .. unless you count not sleeping for 3 days hard LOL..<br><br>IX is easy as pie.. King is fairly easy .. just getting to him can be tuff...   Once again sorry for my interuption but had to let you know you were mistaken about cleric Epic involving PoA.<br><br>I should know I have a 55 cleric who has half his epic done ..  <p>Prub<Br> Mighty Slayer of beasties<Br